  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "WHO declares a global health emergency",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Health Organization (WHO) has moved to activate its highest alert level for the growing monkeypox epidemic.",
        "The virus has been declared a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC), says WHO Director-General Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus.",
        "The emergency committee did not reach a consensus, but the decision was taken after the WHO expert group held a second meeting to discuss the situation.",
        "Tedros explained that monkeypox outbreaks are currently concentrated among men who have sex with men, particularly those with multiple sexual partners.",
        "He further said that this is an epidemic that can be stopped with the right strategies of the right groups.",
        "A recent study has also revealed that the global monkeypox epidemic, which has affected nearly 17,000 people in 74 countries, is primarily driven by sex between men."
      ],
